# IBEX Harness — Root Cursor Rules
# Production-grade AI agent memory and context management platform
# Target: Fortune 500 / MAANG-acceptable code quality

## MANDATORY: Read before any task

Before generating or editing code, read and apply the matching rules in
`.cursor/rules/`. Cursor loads them via each file's YAML frontmatter:

- `alwaysApply: true` — injected into every agent session (listed below).
- `alwaysApply: false` + `globs: [...]` — apply when your edits touch
  matching paths (listed below). If you edit Go proxy code, 01–05, 15, 19,
  24, and 29 all apply.

Also read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for repo workflow and security constraints.

Do not strip `description`, `globs`, or `alwaysApply` from `.mdc` frontmatter.
Rules with `alwaysApply: false` and no `globs` are dead — never ship that.

